Creating a collection of a flipped blue chip collection only? NGMI, CryptoPhunks V1 was a cash grab. The original devs are gone and are no longer affiliated. The value comes from the community of builders that was created around it due to the its unique history and story.

13/13

The @CryptoPhunksV2 community is ğŸ”¥ and the development is just getting started. Don't believe me? Check out their Discord by yourself: https://t.co/TReMsusewN

12/13

"People wouldn't brag about having a fake Rolex" Oh, they would if that fake Rolex was also very limited (10k created) and worked great and even much better than the original Rolex.

11/13

They get the next best thing.
AltPunks - All alternative punks market is going to be very big. Some collections will be valuable, some will be less valuable, exactly like Bitcoin alternatives. An alt doesn't need to flip it's OG to become valuable on it's own.

10/13

Psychology: NFT derivatives is a big market and will be a huge market. There are only 10k punks but the NFT ecosystem is growing in thousands by the day. Supply is constant while demand is increasing. What do people do when they can't get something?

9/13

"Devs are just making money from it now". There's a 0% secondary fee on https://t.co/NlQoUUxDlX, NEXT

8/13

You may support the cause or you may think @NotLarvaLabs are riding on this story in order to force legitimacy on the project. Regardless, surviving the delisting and growing from it is an historical event.

7/13

While NFTs are seen as a way to fight centralization, we are far from it. The DMCA forcing Opensea to take it down is a big centralized move that should have killed any collection, as Opensea has a monopoly on the NFT market (for now). Phunks survived it and grew from it.

6/13

The community created https://t.co/NlQoUUxDlX, a new marketplace for CryptoPhunks and it blew up in traction. Ironically, the attempts of @larvalabs at keeping them down made CryptoPhunks a symbol of taking the centralization fight to a whole other level.

5/13

The community pointed out that the project is legit and it is a very obvious satire of punks and not an attempt to make traders confused and buy them by mistake. A letter to Larva Labs was published which expended on that matter

4/13 https://t.co/ScFlyyZ7yP

History: CryptoPhunks were delisted from @opensea 3 times and got a DMCA letter from @larvalabs several times. Devs didn't want to deal with the situation and ran off with the money and yet, the community didn't fall apart.

3/13

At first they look like mirrored punks and that's not true at all, they also have a frame! But seriously, we should know by now that the NFT token itself is far more than its (centralized) image. So why do CryptoPhunks have a strong position in the NFT market? Here's why:
